.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705184,"age":2,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705185,"age":12,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Alice De Gernon Countess Of Hertford was born in 1094, in Normandy, France as the daughter of Lucia Countess Of Chester, Of Mercia, Of Bolingbroke, De Taillebois Lucy Thoroldsdottir. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Robert de Condet Lord of Thorngate. She died in 1148, in Skelton, Yorkshire, England, at the age of 54."},"et":{"1094–1148":"1094–1148","1106–1141":"1106–1141","1138–1201":"1138–1201","1141–1186":"1141–1186","1074–1136":"1074–1136","1106":"1106","1138":"1138","1148":"1148","1136":"1136","1201":"1201","10 October 114